ebooks.org/lamp-chinese/ \u8ddf\u8457\u8d70\uff0c\u5c31\u6210\u4f5b The Lamp for the Path of Enlightenment]''' (Commentary)\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/\u6211\u9858\u7121\u76e1/ \u6211\u9858\u7121\u76e1 The King of Aspirations]''' (Commentary)\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/dancer-of-great-bliss/ \u0f56\u0f51\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f41\u0f53\u0f0d \u0f0d \u0f58\u0f41\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f74\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f41\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5a\u0f7c\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa3\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f99\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0fa1\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0d \u2022 Dancer of Great Bliss: Essential Life Story of Ts\u00fcltrim Gyamtso Rinpoche \u2022 \u5927\u6a02\u821e\u8005 : \u7af9\u6e05\u5609\u63aa\u4ec1\u6ce2\u5207]'''\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/thrangu/ \u0f42\u0f5e\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f74\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5a\u0f7c\u0f0d \u0f0d \u0f58\u0f41\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f41\u0fb2\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f42\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa3\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f99\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0fa1\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0d \u2022 Ocean of Philosophy: Essential Life Story of Khenchen Thrangu Rinpoche \u2022 \u7d93\u6559\u5927\u6d77 : \u5275\u53e4\u4ec1\u6ce2\u5207]'''\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/3tenga/ \u0f58\u0f50\u0f7c\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f7c\u0f51\u0f0d \u0f0d \u0f62\u0fa1\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fb3\u0f7c\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0f9f\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f42\u0f60\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa3\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f99\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f66\u0fa1\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0d \u2022 Transmission by Seeing: Essential Life Story of Dorlop Tenga Rinpoche \u2022 \u898b\u50b3\u5bf6\u85cf : \u5929\u5676\u4ec1\u6ce2\u5207]'''\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/12situpa/ \u0f56\u0fb1\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f55\u0fb2\u0f74\u0f63\u0f0d \u0f0d \u0f56\u0fb1\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f42\u0f7c\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fad\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f4f\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f64\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f4f\u0f71\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f4f\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa3\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f99\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f4f\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0d Magical Illusion of the Great Maitreya: The Essential Life Story of Jamg\u00f6n Kenting Goshir Tai Situ Rinpoche]'''\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/12gyaltsab/ \u0f42\u0f66\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f51\u0f42\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7c\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f62\u0f0d \u0f0d \u0f58\u0f5a\u0f74\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f55\u0f74\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f51\u0fb2\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f64\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f5a\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa3\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f50\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f99\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f4f\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0d Lord of the Secret Teachings\u2019 Dynamic Display: The Essential Life Story of Drungpa Tsurphu Goshir Gyaltsap Rinpoche]'''\n\n'''2017-2019: [https://dharmaebooks.org/kagyu-monlam-book/ The Kagyu Monlam Book: A Compilation for Recitation]'''\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/kmbtibetan/ \u0f56\u0f40\u0f60\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fa8\u0f7c\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f7a\u0f56\u0f0d]\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/\u5676\u8209\u5927\u7948\u9858-\u6cd5\u6703\u8ab2\u8aa6\u672c/ \u5676\u8209\u5927\u7948\u9858 \u6cd5\u6703\u8ab2\u8aa6\u672c]\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/kagju-mynlam-modlitwy-i-rytualy/ Kagju Mynlam: modlitwy i rytua\u0142y]\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/kagyu-monlam-russian/ \u041a\u043d\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0432 \u041a\u0430\u0433\u044c\u044e \u041c\u043e\u043d\u043b\u0430\u043ca]\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/el-libro-del-monlam-kagyu/ El Libro del Monlam Kagyu]\n\n'''2017: [https://dharmaebooks.org/drubtha/ \u0f42\u0fb2\u0f74\u0f56\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f50\u0f60\u0f0b\u0f51\u0fad\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f74\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f7a\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f53\u0f0d \u0f66\u0f7a\u0f58\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f59\u0f58\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f66\u0f90\u0f7c\u0f62\u0f0d The Philosophical Schools: The Ornament Beautifying the Dakpo Lineage]''' (Mind Only)\n\n'''2017-2018: [https://wisdomexperience.org/product/interconnected-paperback/ Interconnected: Embracing Life in Our Global Society]'''\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/interconnected-russian/ \u0412\u0437\u0430\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0432\u044f\u0437\u044c]\n\n'''2003-2017: [https://www.namsebangdzo.com/Music-in-the-Sky-p/9788178221939.htm Music in the Sky]'''\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/muzyka-na-niebie/ Muzyka na Niebie]\n\n'''2016: [https://dharmaebooks.org/\u0f56\u0f66\u0fa1\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f56\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42/ \u0f56\u0f66\u0fa1\u0f74\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f56\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f66\u0f74\u0f58\u0f0d The Radiant Smile of Jamyang Zhepa]'''\n\n'''2015: [https://karmapafoundation.eu/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Nurturing-Compassion_ENG.pdf Nurturing Compassion]''' (Teachings from the First Visit to Europe)\n\n* [https://karmapafoundation.eu/kfe-publications/nurturing-compassion/ Available in 13 languages]\n\n'''2013-2014: The Heart Is Noble: Changing the World from the Inside Out''' ([https://www.namsebangdzo.com/Heart-Is-Noble-Changing-the-World-from-the-Inside-p/9781611800807.htm print] | [https://www.amazon.com/Heart-Noble-Changing-World-Inside-ebook/dp/B00BSZUCOK/ref=sr_1_1?keywords=The+Heart+is+Noble&qid=1570771482&sr=8-1 ebook])\n\n* [https://www.namsebangdzo.com/Heart-is-Noble-23815-39640-20043-24515-p/9789866091209.htm \u5d07\u9ad8\u4e4b\u5fc3]\n* [https://www.namsebangdzo.com/Heart-Is-Noble-Changing-the-World-from-the-Inside-p/9788478089062.htm Corazon es Noble Como Cambiar el Mundo Desde Dentro Hacia Fuera]\n\n'''2007-2011: [http://www.ktdpublications.com/kagyu-monlam-books/ The Kagyu Monlam Book]'''\n\n'''2009: [https://www.namsebangdzo.com/Future-Is-Now-p/15858.htm The Future is Now: Timely Advice for Creating a Better World]'''\n\n'''2009: [http://www.ktdpublications.com/traveling-the-path-of-compassion/ Traveling the Path of Compassion: A Commentary on The Thirty-Seven Practices of a Bodhisattva]'''\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/na-sciezce-wspolczucia/ Na \u015bcie\u017cce wsp\u00f3\u0142czucia]\n\n'''2006: [http://www.ktdpublications.com/ceremony-of-offering/ Ceremony of Offering to the Gurus]'''<ref>This list may not include ''all'' publications by Ogyen Trinley Dorje; in particular, titles published in Chinese.</ref>\n\n== Controversy ==\n{{Main|Karmapa controversy}}\n[[Mipham Chokyi Lodro]], 14th [[Shamarpa]] (the second-longest recognized tulku lineage in the Karma Kagyu tradition, and who in previous incarnations has held and transmitted the Kagyu lineage between Karmapas), did not recognize Ogyen Trinley Dorje and instead proclaimed [[Trinley Thaye Dorje]] ({{bo|w=Mtha'-yas Rdo-rje}}), whom he purportedly identified a few years earlier than the recognition of Orgyen Thrinley Dorje in a dream as the true Karmapa. Shamarpas camp argue that until the reincarnation line of the Shamarpas was forbidden by the government of the Dalai Lama,<ref>see: [[Shamarpa#Controversy]]</ref> the successive Shamarpas were the persons in charge to recognize the Karmapas, whereas the [[Dalai Lama]]s played no role in the recognition.<ref>[https://karmapaissue.wordpress.com/affirmation-of-prof-samuel-geoffrey-concerning-the-historical-role-of-the-dalai-lamas-in-recognizing-the-karmapas/ Prof. Geoffrey Brian Samuel in: \u201cAffirmation of Geoffrey Brian Samuel,\u201d Lama vs. Hope and Ors, CIV-2004404-001363, High Court of New Zealand Auckland Registry, 11 November 2004].</ref>\n\nMany of the previous Karmapas have left a letter stating the details of their rebirth (this is an aspect of the special self-recognizing [[siddhi]] of the Karmapas) to assist in the recognition of their future incarnation, and thus the Shamarpa's recognition through a dream has come under scrutiny. On the other side Shamarpa questioned the authenticity of the \"prophecy letter\" which the 16th Karmapa allegedly had written and asked Situ Rinpoche for a forensic test of the letter, which Situ Rinpoche refused.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://karmapaissue.wordpress.com/2015/03/10/the-letter-of-prediction/ |title = The \"letter of prediction\"|date = 10 March 2015}}</ref> Ogyen Trinley Dorje is supported by the majority of the Kagyu hierarchy,<ref>{{cite news |title=Tibetan Lama Faces Scrutiny and Suspicion in India |first=Jim |last=Yardley |authorlink=Jim Yardley |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/08/world/asia/08tibet.html?pagewanted=all |newspaper=New York Times |date=8 February 2011 |accessdate=8 February 2011 |quote=After the death of the previous Karmapa, a bitter feud broke out between the high lamas charged with identifying his successor: at least two other people now claim to be the Karmapa, though a majority of Tibetans, including the Dalai Lama, recognize Ogyen Trinley Dorje. |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wM5g7lzg?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/08/world/asia/08tibet.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all |archivedate=8 February 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> including two lamas who have played a role in finding previous Karmapas: [[Tai Situpa]] and [[Goshir Gyaltsab]]. A fourth such lama, the 3rd [[Jamgon Kongtrul]], died early on during the controversy. Ogyen Trinley Dorje was enthroned at [[Tsurphu Monastery]].\n\nOther high Kagyu lamas who support Ogyen Trinley Dorje include the 9th [[Traleg Kyabgon Rinpoche]];{{Citation needed|date=February 2011}} the 9th [[Thrangu Rinpoche]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rinpoche.com/controversy.htm |title=The Karmapa Controversy |work=HomePage of Thrangu Rinpoche |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wM6qZszC?url=http://www.rinpoche.com/controversy.htm |archivedate=9 February 2011 |accessdate=8 February 2011 |quote=I have concluded with absolute certainty that Urgyen Trinley Drodul Dorje from Tibet is the 17th Karmapa. |url-status=dead }}</ref> the 7th [[Dzogchen Ponlop Rinpoche]] and his [[Nalandabodhi]] organization;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nalandabodhi.org/teachers/lineage-masters.aspx |title=Lineage Masters |year=2009 |work=Nalandabodhi: Gateway to the Buddhist Science of Mind |publisher=Nalandabodhi |accessdate=8 February 2011}}</ref> the 12th Surmang [[Choseng Trungpa]]; the 7th [[Yongey Mingyur Rinpoche]];{{Citation needed|date=February 2011}} the 3rd [[Tenga Rinpoche]]; [[Khenpo Karthar Rinpoche]] (abbot of [[Karma Triyana Dharmachakra]]);<ref>[http://www.kagyu.org/gallery/index.php?ktora=ktd&year=2008&cat_id=280]</ref> [[Sakyong Mipham]] and his organization, [[Shambhala Buddhism]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shambhala.org/community/2008/karmapa.php |title=Shambhala Welcomes His Holiness the Seventeenth Karmapa to America! |year=2008 |work=shambhala.org |publisher=Shambhala International (Vajradhatu) |location=Halifax, Nova Scotia |accessdate=8 February 2011}}</ref> Drupon Rinpoche and Lama Norlha Rinpoche, among others. He is also recognized as Karmapa by both the current [[14th Dalai Lama]] and the government of [[China]].\n\nAlso sided with Orgyen Trinley Dorje are tulkus he has identified, such as the 11th [[Nenang Pawo]], and those identified by Tai Situ Rinpoche such as the 3rd [[Kalu Rinpoche]]. There are now two recognitions of the 4th [[Jamgon Kongtrul]], one sided with each Karmapa.\n\n=== 2011 police raid on Karmapa offices ===\n\nIn January 2011, the Himachal Pradesh Police seized money in currencies of 25 countries including China, valued at over {{INR}} 60 million, during raids on the offices of a trust backed by Ogyen Trinley Dorje.<ref>{{cite news\n| url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/article1134697.ece\n| title = Foreign currency seized from monastery\n| publisher = The Hindu\n| date = 29 January 2011\n| accessdate = 29 January 2011\n| location=Chennai, India\n}}</ref> They also seized several [[traveler's cheque]]s and land deal documents, suspecting a [[hawala]] scam. Initially, the police suspected that the money was being used to spread Chinese influence in India, and that the Karmapa was a Chinese agent helping the Chinese government control Buddhist monasteries in India.<ref>{{cite news\n| url = http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_money-stashing-karmapa-may-be-tried_1500335\n| title = Money-stashing karmapa may be tried\n| publisher = [[DNA (newspaper)|DNA]]\n| author1 = Vineeta Pandey \n| author2 = Ajay Bharadwaj \n| date = 29 January 2011\n| accessdate = 29 January 2011\n}}</ref> They said even if the Karmapa was able to explain the source of the money recovered, he might be held liable for violating the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act.<ref name=\"DNAINDIA\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report_no-clue-about-the-cash-karmapa_1500661 |title=No clue about the cash:Karmapa|publisher=DNAINDIA |accessdate=29 January 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe Karmapa denied all the allegations and said that the seized money came via the donations from his followers.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.hindu.com/2011/02/01/stories/2011020158031500.htm | title = China denies Karmapa links, Tibetans express anger | author = Ananth Krishnan | date = 29 January 2011 | accessdate = 1 February 2011 | publisher = [[The Hindu]] | location=Chennai, India}}</ref> A ''New York Times'' report on the matter noted that an unnamed rival Karmapa candidate has \"close ties to Indian intelligence officials.\"<ref>{{cite news | title = China: Officials Say Tibetan Lama Is Not a Chinese Spy as India Says | first = Edward | last = Wong | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/05/world/asia/05briefs-China.html | newspaper = New York Times | date = 4 February 2011 | accessdate = 8 February 2011 | archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5wM5CQfF3?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/05/world/asia/05briefs-China.html?_r=1 | archivedate = 8 February 2011 | url-status = dead }}</ref> On 11 February 2011, it was reported that the central Indian government had cleared the Karmapa of all charges, finding that the money in question had been donated by followers.<ref>\"[https://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/12/world/asia/12briefs-India.html India: Tibetan Lama Cleared in Cash Inquiry, Report Says].\" The New York Times, 11 February 2011.</ref>\n\nIn December 2011, the Himachal Pradesh Police filed a chargesheet against Ogyen Trinley Dorje, naming him as an accused in the cash and foreign currency seizure case.<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/n/a/2011/12/08/international/i003657S56.DTL India police charge Tibet holy man in money probe]. San Francisco Chronicle, 8 December 2011.</ref> The Karmapa's office claimed that Dorje was not involved in the financial administration.<ref>[http://www.indianexpress.com/news/-Karmapa-not-involved-in-financial-administration-of-office-/885568/ \u2018Karmapa not involved in financial administration of office\u2019]. Indian Express, 9 December 2011.</ref>\n\n====Charges dropped====\nIndian police said on Tuesday 24 April 2012 that they had dropped all criminal charges against Ogyen Trinley Dorje.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://au.news.yahoo.com/thewest/a/-/world/13513919/india-drops-charges-against-top-tibetan-monk/|title=The West Australian}}</ref>\n\n====Criminal proceedings opened====\nA judge at the Himachal Pradesh High Court issued an order for authorities to open criminal proceedings over the recovery of around 1 million USD in foreign currency during a raid on his Buddhist monastery. His spokesman stated that \"He strongly believes truth will prevail at the end\".<ref>http://news.sky.com/story/1515983/top-tibetan-monk-on-money-laundering-charge</ref>\nKarmapa, along with nine other accused, was charged on 7 December 2012 and was asked by the court to appear personally on 6 March 2013. He failed to appear as he was out of Dharamsala. All the accused were {{Asof|2015|07|lc=y}} on bail.<ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/karmapa-ogyen-trinley-dorje-suffers-high-court-blow/1/450133.html Start Criminal Proceedings against Karmapa: Himachal HC to Govt], in ''[[India Today]]'', 9 July 2015, Retrieved 26 November 2018</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Karmapa controversy]]\n* [[Kagyu]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n* ''The Dance of 17 Lives : The Incredible True Story of Tibet's 17th Karmapa'', by Mick Brown. New York, NY: Bloomsbury USA, 2005. {{ISBN|1-58234-598-8}}\n* ''Music in the Sky: The Life, Art & Teachings of the 17th Karmapa Ogyen Trinley Dorje'', by Michele Martin.  Ithaca, New York: Snow Lion Press, 2003.  {{ISBN|1-55939-195-2}}.\n* ''Karmapa of Tibet: The Politics of Reincarnation'', by Lea Terhune. Somerville, MA: Wisdom Publications, 2004. {{ISBN|0-86171-180-7}}\n* [http://www.facenfacts.com/NewsDetails/18612/tibet-vulnerable-to-climate-change-says-karmapa.htm  Tibet vulnerable to climate change] ( FacenFacts)\n* [http://www.kagyu.org/ Karma Triyana Dharmachakra \u2013 The Office of Ogyen Trinley Dorje's center and branches in the United States] (re-retrieved 1 February 2011)\n* [http://www.ted.com/talks/lang/eng/his_holiness_the_karmapa_the_technology_of_the_heart.html TED.com Talk: \"The technology of the heart\" (Live via interpreter), Nov 2009] (retrieved 1 February 2011)\n* [http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/the-karmapa-breaks-his-silence/358897/ \"The Karmapa breaks his silence\"] Business Standard article dated 23 May 2009 (re-retrieved 1 February 2011)\n* [http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1807103,00.html TIME Magazine article on Karmapa] Time.com, 15 May 2008 (re-retrieved 1 February 2011)\n* [http://whoiskarmapa.com/ Who Is Karmapa (Karmapa is coming to the USA!)] (re-retrieved 1 February 2011)\n* [http://www.simhas.org/ The 17th Karmapa Ogyen Trinley Dorje at Simhas.org] (retrieved 1 February 2011)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070223012938/http://www.karmapa.net/ 17th Karmapa Ogyen Trinley Dorje Links at Karmapa.net] (re-retrieved 1 February 2011)\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n*[https://www.facebook.com/AryaKshema/ Arya Kshema]\n*[https://adarsha.dharma-treasure.org Adarsha]\n*[http://dharmaebooks.org Dharma Ebooks]\n*[https://dharma-treasure.org Dharma Treasure]\n*{{TED speaker|2=His Holiness the Karmapa}}\n*[http://www.kagyumonlam.org/ Kagyu Monlam]\n*[https://digital-toolbox.dharma-treasure.org Ketaka]\n*[http://www.khoryug.com Khoryug]\n*[https://issuu.com/layjang Layjang \u2013 Karmapa's Office Bulletin]\n*[https://www.facebook.com/karmapa Official Facebook page]\n*[https://www.instagram.com/karmapa/ Official Instagram page]\n*[https://twitter.com/karmapa17 Official Twitter page]\n*{{Official website|http://www.kagyuoffice.org/}}\n*[https://www.youtube.com/user/Karmapateachings Official YouTube channel]\n*[https://kagyuoffice.org/karmapa-podcast/ Podcasts]\n*[https://kagyuoffice.org/teachings/ Teachings]\n*[https://kagyuoffice.org/karmapa-videos/ Video Library]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-rel|bu}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Rangjung Rigpe Dorje]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Karmapa|Reincarnation of the Karmapa]]<br /><sup>Co-claimant along with [[Thaye Dorje]]</sup>|years=1992-present<br />Recognized in 1992}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{Karmapas}}\n{{Buddhism topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dorje, Ogyen Trinley}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Lamas]]\n[[Category:21st-century Tibetan people]]\n[[Category:Buddhist monks from Tibet]]\n[[Category:Karmapa claimants|*]]\n[[Category:Lamas from Tibet]]\n[[Category:Rinpoches]]\n[[Category:Tibetan dissidents]]\n[[Category:Tibetan environmentalists]]\n[[Category:Tibetan Lamas]]\n[[Category:Tibetan poets]]\n[[Category:Tibetan writers]]\n[[Category:Tulkus]]\n[[Category:Buddhist vegetarianism]]\n[[Category:Vegetarianism activists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Tibetan Lama}}\n{{Advert|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox religious biography\n| background = #FFD068\n| name = Ogyen Trinley Dorje\n| image= Karmapa lama.JPG\n| caption =\n| birth_name = Apo Gaga\n| alias =\n| dharma name =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1985|6|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Chamdo County]], [[Tibet]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| nationality =\n| religion = [[Vajrayana]]\n| school = [[Karma Kagyu]]\n| lineage =\n| title = His Holiness<br />17th Karmapa<sup>Co-claimant along with [[Thaye Dorje]]</sup>\n| location =\n| education =\n| occupation =\n| teacher =\n| reincarnation of = [[Karmapa]]<sup>Co-claimant along with [[Thaye Dorje]]</sup>\n| predecessor = [[Rangjung Rigpe Dorje]]\n| successor =\n| students =\n| spouse =\n| partner =\n| children =\n| website = {{URL | kagyuoffice.org | KagyuOffice.org }}\n}}{{Tibetan Buddhism}}\n'''Ogyen Trinley Dorje''' ({{bo-tw|t=\u0f68\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f55\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa1\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f97\u0f7a\u0f0d|w=O-rgyan 'Phrin-las Rdo-rje}}, {{zh|c=\u9114\u91d1\u6b3d\u5217\u591a\u5091}}; born 26 June 1985), also written '''Urgyen Trinley Dorje''' ({{bo|w=U-rgyan 'Phrin-las Rdo-rje}}; is a [[Karmapa controversy|claimant to the title]] of 17th Karmapa Lama.\n\nThe [[Karmapa]] is head of the [[Karma Kagyu]] school, one of the four main schools of [[Tibetan Buddhism]].\n\n== Biography ==\nBorn in Lhatok Township, [[Chamdo County]], [[Tibet Autonomous Region]], [[China]], to primarily [[nomad]]ic parents,<ref name=\"ctic\">{{Cite news |url=http://chinatibet.people.com.cn/6636399.html |title=Reincarnation and enthronement of the 17th Living Buddha Karmapa |date=14 April 2009 |accessdate=17 August 2010 |publisher=China Tibet Information Center}}</ref> Ogyen Trinley Dorje is said to have identified himself to family members as the Karmapa early in childhood. Known as Apo Gaga, he was seven years old before he was recognized by a search party headed by the [[Tai Situpa]], following instructions Situpa claims were left to him by the previous Karmapa in a prophetic letter hidden in a locket. Ogyen Trinley Dorje was installed at [[Tsurphu Monastery]] ({{bo|w=Mtshur-phu}}), the traditional seat of the Karmapa in [[Tibet]], recognized by both the [[14th Dalai Lama]] and the official sanction of the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China]], who declared him to be a \"living Buddha\", the first time the China's communist government has officially confirmed a [[tulku]]. Already a year later the Chinese announced during the UN-Human Rights Conference in Vienna, that they would train him in Tsurphu for his future task as successor of the Dalai Lama.<ref>\"Die Presse\", 17 June 1993, page 2:  \"Am Rande der Konferenz\".</ref>\n\nAt the age of 14, he escaped to [[India]] through [[Nepal]],<ref>{{cite press release |title=Press Statement from the 17 year old Karmapa Ogyen Trinley Dorje April 27, 2001, Gyuto Ramoche Tantric University, Sidbhari, Distt. Kangra, HP, India |publisher=Worldbridges Tibet |date=27 April 2001 |url=http://worldbridges.com/Tibet/features/karmapa042701/index.html |accessdate=16 March 2008}}</ref> arriving at the Tibetan exile quarters at [[McLeod Ganj]] on 5 January 2000.  Ogyen Trinley Dorje had felt that he was unable to obtain in China the specialized instruction he needed to complete his studies and to realize his full spiritual authority. He resides at [[Gyuto Order|Gyuto Monastery]] in [[Sidhbari]], near [[Dharamshala]].\n\nFrom 15 May 15 to 2 June 2008, he made his first trip to the West, visiting several cities in the [[United States]] (notably [[New York City]], [[Boulder, Colorado]], and [[Seattle]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kagyu.org/kagyulineage/karmapa/visit2008/index.php|title=His Holiness the 17th Karmapa's visit to his North American Seat in the USA}}</ref> and was formally enthroned in the North American seat of the Karmapas at [[Karma Triyana Dharmachakra]] monastery in [[Woodstock, New York]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uVcje0t3-nE|title=YouTube video}}</ref> All across the country, he gave multiple teachings on [[compassion]] and [[Environmentalism|the environment]], gave the reading transmission for a new form of [[ng\u00f6ndro]], and bestowed several [[Empowerment (Vajrayana)|empowerments]], including those of [[Avalokite\u015bvara]] and [[Padmasambhava]]. He also spoke about the special challenges of the rapid pace of modern society, and the virtues of the [[Internet]] as a tool for the study and practice of [[Buddhism]].\n\nIn July 2008 he requested permission to visit monasteries in [[Lahaul and Spiti district]] in [[Himachal Pradesh]] and in [[Ladakh]] in [[Jammu and Kashmir]]. The [[Government of India]] initially refused to allow these visits without giving a reason. It was speculated that the reason might have been that these areas are close to the border with China and that the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] were approaching even though the Karmapa had made it clear that he does not promote Tibetan independence and has no political stance on China.<ref>[http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/uncategorized/tibetan-spiritual-leader-not-allowed-to-go-near-china-border_10075287.html Tibetan spiritual leader not allowed to go near China border]</ref> India eventually allowed his tour, which began in Ladakh, followed by Lahaul and Spiti, including the famous [[Tabo Monastery]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=22734&article=India+Okays+Karmapa%e2%80%99s+Visit+to+Border+Areas|title=India Okays Karmapa\u2019s Visit to Border Areas}}</ref>\n[[File:Karmapa Urgyen Trinley Dorje1.jpg|thumb|200px|Ogyen Trinley Dorje at age 14]]\n\nRequests to visit USA and Europe in 2010 were denied by the Indian government.\n\nOn 9 July 2011, Dorje arrived back in the United States for his second visit. From 9 to 17 July, he participated in the [[Kalachakra]] initiation bestowed by the [[14th Dalai Lama]] in [[Washington, D.C.]], then traveled by train to his seat at Karma Triyana Dharmachakra and also visited both his center in [[New Jersey]] and [[Hunter College]] in New York City, returning to India on 4 August. During his visit, he taught extensively on compassion, gave [[Refuge (Buddhism)|Refuge]], and bestowed the empowerments of both the Four-Armed and Thousand-Armed forms of Avalokite\u015bvara. He also granted an interview with [[Laurie Goodstein]] of ''[[The New York Times]]'', which was published on 28 July 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/29/us/29lama.html?_r=1 |work=The New York Times |first=Laurie |last=Goodstein |title=A Young Lama Prepares to Be a Tibetan Leader |date=28 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n{{as of|2018|October}}, Ogyen Trinley Dorje was residing in the United States [https://www.buddhistdoor.net/news/karmapa-extends-stay-in-us-health-concerns-cited] and had been outside of India continuously since May 2017. In 2018, in order to facilitate travel abroad, he became a citizen of the Caribbean nation of [[Dominica]] [https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/himachal/karmapa-now-a-dominican-citizen/695631.html] through a provision allowing citizenship through investment.[https://www.imidaily.com/caribbean/likely-successor-to-dalai-lama-gets-dominica-citizenship-by-investment/]\n\n== Reconciliation: Healing Divisions within the Karma Kagyu Lineage ==\n\n=== 2018: The Claimants Meet for the First Time ===\nOn 10 and 11 Oct 2018, in rural France, Ogyen Trinley Dorje (OTD) and [[Trinley Thaye Dorje]] (TTD) met each other in person for the first time.\n\nA [https://kagyuoffice.org/joint-statement-of-his-holiness-ogyen-trinley-dorje-and-his-holiness-trinley-thaye-dorje/ joint statement] by OTD<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/joint-statement-of-his-holiness-ogyen-trinley-dorje-and-his-holiness-trinley-thaye-dorje/|title=Joint Statement of His Holiness Ogyen Trinley Dorje and His Holiness Trinley Thaye Dorje {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> and  TTD<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.karmapa.org/joint-statement-of-his-holiness-trinley-thaye-dorje-and-his-holiness-ogyen-trinley-dorje/|title=Joint statement of His Holiness Trinley Thaye Dorje and His Holiness Ogyen Trinley Dorje|date=11 October 2018|website=The 17th Karmapa: Official website of Thaye Dorje, His Holiness the 17th Gyalwa Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> was released on 11 October 2018, via their respective websites, and was circulated using various social media outlets. The notable event was subsequently reported by numerous Buddhist and secular media sources.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lionsroar.com/two-claimants-to-karmapa-title-release-joint-statement-reunify-lineage/|title=Two claimants to \"Karmapa\" title release joint statement calling for unity|last=Atwood|first=Haleigh|date=11 October 2018|website=Lion's Roar|language=en-US|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tricycle.org/trikedaily/karmapas-meet/|title=Karmapas Unite|last=Lefferts|first=Gabriel|date=11 October 2018|website=Tricycle: The Buddhist Review|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tibetanjournal.com/two-karmapas-meet-first-time-france-issues-joint-statement/|title=Two Karmapas Meet for the First Time in France, Issues Joint Statement|last=editor|first=T. J.|date=12 October 2018|website=Tibetan Journal|language=en-US|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/in-a-first-two-claimants-to-karmapa-title-meet-for-talks/articleshow/66172015.cms|title=In a first, two claimants to Karmapa title meet for talks {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=12 Oct|first=TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2018|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019|last3=Ist|first3=2:34}}</ref> The event prompted several reactions,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tibetsun.com/news/2018/10/11/reactions-from-tibet-experts-on-karmapa-meeting|title=Reactions from Tibet experts on Karmapa meeting .:. Tibet Sun|website=www.tibetsun.com|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://theprint.in/opinion/2-karmapas-are-uniting-and-its-time-for-india-to-deal-with-it-in-a-mature-way/134917/|title=2 Karmapas are uniting and it's time for India to deal with it in a mature way|last=Stobdan|first=P.|date=10 December 2018|work=The Print|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> including statements of support from [[Gyalwang Drukpa]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/Gyalwang.Drukpa/posts/2111065092266438|title=Gyalwang Drukpa|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> [https://www.facebook.com/HE-Goshir-Gyaltsab-Rinpoche-131893913518258/ Goshir Gyaltsap Rinpoche],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2498586833515609&id=131893913518258|title=HE Goshir Gyaltsab Rinpoche|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> [https://www.facebook.com/nyima20/?__xts__&#x5B;0&#x5D;=68.ARAU9C7LxUr0DEAFdxw_GdanuR2RLVk5JiD_CXk-iOvyZ0e7rb3deW_RxK-mRMg9Azm3ov873A9vriCxUrYsJ696KRdRvF9V-EhkofsLgt4ImKNWR_H5NG6HQfvJVispHLoompiF4yjHaKDobhzdpTt-qUBFCEQQl1dNFJdGJ7ldBF2r8EQoo7QGxOn8rHQ473tcvEMiYbP5msf8qQetHuSMc2F7qMyu1thQMs-Uzt5BFxTEzYdHHf4ZLyd1EToWo--5Oje0WKD1KE99IBOkvvGVHngu5kbjraVWQ6RMcEB_FrIFnSNQCeDP2ylb8RMnM99wjsS-SI-87waTfDN1sQ Jamgon Kongtrul Rinpoche],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/nyima20/posts/1914731635300441|title=Jamgon Kongtrul|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> [https://www.facebook.com/BeruKhyentseRinpoche/ Beru Khyentse Rinpoche],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/BeruKhyentseRinpoche/photos/a.901120299900608/2181829991829626/?type=3|title=His Eminence Beru Khyentse Rinpoche|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref> and [[Zurmang Gharwang Rinpoche]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/zurmang.gharwang/posts/916325548556809|title=Zurmang Gharwang Rinpoche|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 October 2018, during a [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D_E4X0sh2mQ&t=1846 publicly webcasted video address], Ogyen Trinley Dorje gave further explanation about his recent meetings with Trinley Thaye Dorje in France, and his reason/motivation for doing so. OTD expressed how the Karma Kamtsang forefathers and disciples maintained and propagated the teachings through study, teaching, and practice; thus, ripened generations of disciples through their wisdom, love, and power. OTD related that this activity of ''ripening'' disciples is the essential heart of the Kagyu history, the majesty and the true weight of the Kagyu teachings. He said that we need to continue to uphold the Lineage by preserving these fine deeds and activities. However, OTD warned, if we instead spend most of our time being biased, factional, and partisan\u2014this is extremely dangerous. If we are partisan and factional, we won't see the faults on our own side, or the qualities on the other. We won't be able to recognize what is good and what is bad. OTD said: \"For that reason, it is a situation where we absolutely must be careful. So this is why I asked His Holiness Thaye Dorje for a meeting this year.\" Furthermore, OTD emphasized that whether reconciliation goes well or not does not depend upon only the two claimants, OTD and TTD. It depends on all the followers and the whole community of the Karma Kamtsang.\n\nIn addition, OTD implored everyone to take as expansive a view as possible, to consider the long-term survival of the Karma Kagyu lineage. He said that those with a very short-term view may think that it was pointless for him to meet with TTD. Likewise, some people might think that OTD, by meeting with TTD, ended up losing\u2014that he was defeated. But he said that victory and defeat is a very short-term worldly way of speaking, and that the long-term danger is that the lineage of the Karma Kagyu will disappear without a trace. Considering this grave danger, OTD said that losing face, victory and defeat, are really not important. In conclusion, OTD requested everyone to please keep this explanation in mind.\n\n=== 2019: Joint Long Life Prayer for Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche\u2019s Reincarnation ===\nOn 27 October 2019 OTD and TTD released a co-authored long life prayer for Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche\u2019s reincarnation. This composition was published on OTD's and TTD's respective websites,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/joint-long-life-prayer-for-kunzig-shamar-rinpoches-reincarnation/|title=\u0f68\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f92\u0fb1\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f55\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa1\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f97\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f0d \u0f55\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f63\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f50\u0f60\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f62\u0fa1\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f97\u0f7a\u0f0b\u0f5f\u0f74\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fa6\u0fb2\u0f7a\u0f63\u0f0b\u0f42\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f5b\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f40\u0f74\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f42\u0f5f\u0f72\u0f42\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f5e\u0fad\u0f0b\u0f51\u0f58\u0f62\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f72\u0f53\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f7c\u0f0b\u0f46\u0f7a\u0f60\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f66\u0fb2\u0f72\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f40\u0fb1\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f5e\u0f56\u0f66\u0f0b\u0f56\u0f62\u0f9f\u0f53\u0f0d Joint long life prayer for Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche's reincarnation by Ogyen Trinley Dorje and Trinley Thaye Dorje. {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=21 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.karmapa.org/joint-long-life-prayer-for-kunzig-shamar-rinpoches-reincarnation-by-trinley-thaye-dorje-and-ogyen-trinley-dorje/|title=Joint long life prayer for Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche's reincarnation by Trinley Thaye Dorje and Ogyen Trinley Dorje|date=27 October 2019|website=The 17th Karmapa: Official website of Thaye Dorje, His Holiness the 17th Gyalwa Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=21 November 2019}}</ref> and circulated via various websites and social media outlets. The unprecedented joint composition was widely circulated, and garnered the support of various Kagyu teachers and communities, including Drikung Kyabgon,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/drikungkyabgon/posts/2559015730847177|title=His Holiness Drikung Kyabgon|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=21 November 2019}}</ref> Rumtek Monastery,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Religious-Center/rumtekgonpa/photos/|title=Rumtek Monastery Page|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=21 November 2019}}</ref> and Karma Drubdey Nunnery.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/karma.drubdey/posts/3385278368179635|title=Karma Drubdey Nunnery|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Dharma Digitization ==\nThe Gyalwang Karmapa has undertaken the important and long-term task of digitizing Buddhist texts so that as many scriptures, commentaries, etc. are available in digital format as possible for future generations, students, scholars and monasteries around the world.\n\nThere are four main websites \u2013 [https://dharma-treasure.org Dharma Treasure], [https://adarsha.dharma-treasure.org Adarsha], [https://digital-toolbox.dharma-treasure.org Ketaka], and [http://dharmaebooks.org Dharma Ebooks] \u2013 each one dealing with a different format, tool, or translation. Adarsha, for example, makes the Kangyur, Tengyur, and Tibetan masterpieces available in digital format and has been catalogued under the guidance of the Gyalwang Karmapa himself.\n\n== Nurturing Tibetan Culture, Unity, Language and Literacy ==\nFor many years Gyalwang Karmapa has emphasized the importance of preserving Tibetan culture, unity, language, and literacy; underlining the importance of sustaining written and spoken Tibetan language, because it is the very root of the Dharma in Tibet and its culture. Tibetan language is the lifeline that links Tibetans to their culture, arts, and spirituality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/the-gyalwang-karmapa-rings-an-alarm-we-must-preserve-tibetan-language-and-culture/|title=The Gyalwang Karmapa Rings an Alarm: We Must Preserve Tibetan Language and Culture {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/the-importance-of-harmony-among-tibetans/|title=The Importance of Harmony among Tibetans {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/a-wide-ranging-interview-with-the-gyalwang-karmapa/|title=A Wide-Ranging Interview with the Gyalwang Karmapa {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref> Tibetan culture, he states, is the mind and life force of the Tibetan people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/language-as-the-link-unity-as-the-future-the-gyalwang-karmapa-speaks-at-the-56th-anniversary-of-the-upper-tcv/|title=Language as the Link, Unity as the Future: The Gyalwang Karmapa Speaks at the 56th Anniversary of the Upper TCV {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nStressing the importance of Tibetan harmony and unity, Gyalwang Karmapa has implored all Tibetans to exercise religious tolerance, stating that all Buddhist traditions in Tibet come from one source, the Buddha, so the differences between them are not great. He has warned that it is a huge mistake to inflate small distinctions into a basis for attachment and hatred, asserting one\u2019s own tradition to be better than another\u2019s. He has said that the reason for any future decline of the Buddha\u2019s Dharma would not come from outside, but from within, from disputes between the holders of his teachings. Therefore, Gyalwang Karmapa has reiterated time and time again that the differences between lineages and factions are minor in terms of view, meditation, and conduct, and has urged everyone to keep a broader non-partisan perspective in mind.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/tibetan-unity-and-language-are-crucial/|title=Tibetan Unity and Language Are Crucial {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 108 Translations ===\n108 Translations was initiated in 2015 by H.H. Karmapa Orgyen Trinley Dorje. Born of a concept developed during a translators\u2019 workshop held at [http://latse.org Latse] and presided over by Gyalwang Karmapa, the aim of the 108 Translations project is to produce a needed body of reading material that can promote the reinvigoration of Tibetan language. Rather than focussing on translating a few famous works that match the interests of a small group of well-educated readers (which has been the case for translations into Tibetan up to the present), 108 Translations aims to provide a plethora of good and easily accessible reading materials for ''average'' Tibetan readers.\n\nIn his [https://dharmaebooks.org/108-translations/ Statement of Purpose], Gyalwang Karmapa expressed that we are currently inhabiting a time where there is great concern that the Tibetan language will go extinct. He has said that we have come to the point where we need to take responsibility for the survival of the Tibetan language, and we are in a situation where there is very little reading material that matches the interests of the ordinary Tibetan reader.\n\nThe main criteria for the 108 Translations is that they don't lose the meaning and feeling (or \"flavour\") of the original, the translations must be easy to understand and pronounce in Tibetan, and the selected works need to meet the interests of the readership. For example, translations of famous literary works that have a low readership are examples of unsuccessful translations. 108 Translations must not only consider how well known the works are, they must also examine how they have sold, how many other languages they have been translated into, and so forth. Works with low sales are not selected, even if they are renowned. Over time, the hope is that future translations will grow ever closer to the interests of the readership.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dharmaebooks.org/108-translations/|title=A Statement of Purpose|last=|first=|date=|website=dharmaebooks.org|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n108 Translations aims to nurture literacy in the Tibetan language, while giving Tibetan readers greater access to world literature. It is a project of Latse and is managed by the 108 Translations Management Team, whose combined skills and experience ensure the highest quality of translation. This project is also generously supported by [https://dharma-treasure.org Dharma Treasure] and the ebooks will be published on [https://dharmaebooks.org/ dharmaebooks.org] as well [http://latse.org/program/108-translations latse.org/program/108-translations].\n\n== Supporting the Female Buddhist Community ==\nThe Karmapa has, for many years, taken a deep interest in the welfare of the female Buddhist community, as well as being a voice that regularly encourages equal rights and opportunities for women practitioners. He has, in particular, taken the responsibility to restore full ordination for Tibetan nuns.\n\nEach year the Karmapa also hosts the [https://www.facebook.com/AryaKshema/ Arya Kshema] dharma winter gathering where nuns receive special teachings, instructions and gather to debate Buddhist philosophy so as to further increase their opportunities for a traditional education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/portfolio-item/nuns-ordination/|title=The Female Buddhist Community {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2013: Preliminary Discussions on Restoring Nuns\u2019 Ordination===\n\nOn 14 September 2013, at the International Buddhist Confederation in New Delhi, Gyalwang Karmapa participated in a discussions with the Full Nun\u2019s Ordination Working Group, joining Co-Chairs Jetsunma Tenzin Palmo, Abbess of Dongyu Gatsal Ling Nunnery in India, and Ven. Dhammananda, Abbess of Wat Songkhammakalayani Temple in Thailand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/gyalwang-karmapa-shares-his-thoughts-on-the-environment-and-bhikshuni-ordination-at-international-buddhist-confederation/|title=Gyalwang Karmapa Shares His Thoughts on the Environment and Bhikshuni Ordination at International Buddhist Confederation {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=13 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015: Gyalwang Karmapa Makes Historic Announcement on Restoring Nuns\u2019 Ordination===\nOn 24 January 2015, during the Second Arya Kshema Winter Dharma Gathering the Gyalwang Karmapa made the historical announcement that, beginning next year [which was later changed to 2017 for astrological reasons], he would take concrete steps<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/gyalwang-karmapa-makes-historic-announcement-on-restoring-nuns-ordination/|title=Gyalwang Karmapa Makes Historic Announcement on Restoring Nuns' Ordination {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=13 October 2019}}</ref><ref>Gyalwang Karmapa explained that: \"over the last ten or twenty years, led by His Holiness the Dalai Lama, many of the masters of Tibetan Buddhism, including many high lamas, geshes, and khenpos, have engaged in discussions with good intentions. There have been many discussions, and people have put great effort into this\u2014I have seen and experienced this for myself. We\u2019ve had a lot of talk and research into the words of the Buddha, the treatises by Indian masters, as well as the Tibetan scriptures. It sometimes seems that over the past twenty years we\u2019ve only had talk and research, but we haven\u2019t actually put anything into practice. It\u2019s been like this for a long time.\"</ref> towards restoring nuns\u2019 vows in the Tibetan Buddhist tradition.\n\n=== 2016: Gyalwang Karmapa Discusses Questions Related to Giving Bhikshuni Ordination to Nuns===\n22 January 2016, during the eighth day of teaching at the Arya Kshema Winter Dharma Gathering, the Gyalwang Karmapa discussed questions related to giving bhikshuni ordination to nuns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/the-gyalwang-karmapa-discusses-nuns-ordination-teaches-on-bodhisattva-vow/|title=The Gyalwang Karmapa Discusses Nuns' Ordination; Teaches on Bodhisattva Vow {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=13 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2017: The First Step Toward Full Ordination for Tibetan Buddhist Nuns ===\n\n==== History of Ordained Nuns in the Tibetan Buddhist Tradition: The Karmapa Relates ====\nIn a [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=la2pK8d0LII video address], Gyalwang Karmapa gave a brief summary of the history of buddhist nuns' ordination and in particular in the Tibetan buddhist tradition. The talk was part of the 4th annual Arya Kshema which took place in Bodhgaya, India.\n\n==== The Special Sramanerika Vow: A Historic Step for Nuns====\n10 March 2017, at the Mahabodhi Stupa, Bodhgaya, Bihar, India, eighteen women took the shramaneri vows. One additional woman would take the vows several days later on the auspicious fifteenth day of the Month of Miracles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kagyuoffice.org/history-in-the-making-the-first-step-toward-full-ordination-for-tibetan-buddhist-nuns/|title=History in the Making: The First Step Toward Full Ordination for Tibetan Buddhist Nuns {{!}} Karmapa \u2013 The Official Website of the 17th Karmapa|language=en-US|access-date=13 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March 2017, on the morning of the first full moon in the Tibetan year, at the sacred site of the Bodhi Tree, the ''Ritual Practice for the Dharma to Flourish in Women\u2019s and Especially Nuns\u2019 Communities'' and the ritual of bestowing the shramaneri vows was successfully completed. Gyalwang Karmapa addressed the assembly.\n\n== Buddhist Vegetarianism ==\n[[File:GYALWA KARMAPA-HST-80x80-IV 08.jpg|left|thumb|200px|\"Gyalwa Karmapa\" (Ogyen Trinley Dorje), by painter [[Claude-Max Lochu]], exhibition for the project of [[Temple for Peace]] in France, 2008]]\n\nOn 3 January 2007, Ogyen Trinley Dorje mandated a purely [[vegetarianism|vegetarian diet]] in all his [[monastery|monasteries]] and centers and strongly urged vegetarianism among all his students, saying that generally, in his view, it was very important in the [[Mahayana]] not to eat meat and that, even in [[Vajrayana]], it is preferable for students and practitioners not to eat meat.<ref>[http://www.shabkar.org/download/pdf/Talk_on_Vegetarianism.pdf Talk on Vegetarianism], by Orgyen Trinle Dorje, Karmapa XVII, As Translated Simultaneously by Ringu Tulku Rinpoche\n3 January 2007, Full Moon Day, During the 24th annual Great Kagyu Monlam, Bodhgaya, India</ref>\n\n== Buddhist Environmentalism ==\nCommenting on the Buddhist tradition of [[life release]], where animals destined for slaughter are bought, blessed and natively released, Orgyen Trinley Dorje indicated that the meaning of this concept was broad and that practitioners should use their intelligence to expand the tradition.<ref name=\"kagyu.org\">{{cite web |url=http://www.kagyu.org/ktd/liferelease.php |title=Life Release |work=Karma Triyana Dharmachakra |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203000250/http://www.kagyu.org/ktd/liferelease.php |archivedate=3 December 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Similarly, when addressing the 2007 Kagyu Monlam Chenmo, he indicated that planting a single tree can be more beneficial than performing life release for many beings; recommending that monasteries should plant one to two thousand trees. In addition he urged monks to practise restraint when sponsors offer technology upgrades.<ref name=\"kagyumonlam.org\">kagyumonlam.org: [http://www.kagyumonlam.org/English/Lectures/20071227_HHK_Advice_Environment.html Kagyu Monlam Chenmo -- Teachings -- More Words on the Environment (2007/12/27)]</ref>\n\nOn [[Earth Day]], on 22 April 2009, Orgyen Trinley Dorje gave 108 instructions on protecting the environment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kagyuoffice.org/Images-09/09-0420-108Solutions/108_Things_to_Do.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101005071531/http://kagyuoffice.org/Images-09/09-0420-108Solutions/108_Things_to_Do.pdf|url-status=dead|title=A Message from the Gyalwang Karmapa: 108 Things You Can Do|archivedate=5 October 2010}}</ref>\n\nAt the second conference on environmental protection (3 to 8 October 2009, [[Gyuto Order|Gyuto Monastery]]), he stated that \"For too long, people have behaved thoughtlessly and ignored the damage to the environment that they are creating and, if this continued there was a great danger that it would be too late to do anything.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=25703|title=Gyuto Monastery in Dharamsala Hosts Conference on Environmental Protection}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 October 2009, Ogyen Trinley Dorje supported [[350.org#International Day of Climate Action|international climate action day]] at a gathering at [[McLeod Ganj]] in northern India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=25798&article=Karmapa+supports+international+climate+action+day&t=1&c=1|title=Karmapa supports international climate action day}}</ref>\n\nIn recent years, [http://www.khoryug.com Khoryug], a network of Tibetan Buddhist monasteries and centers that work on environmental protection in the Eastern Himalayas, was developed under the auspices of Ogyen Trinley Dorje as part of the [[World Wildlife Fund]]'s Sacred Earth: Faiths for Conservation program.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sacred Earth: Faiths for Conservation|url=http://www.worldwildlife.org/initiatives/sacred-earth-faiths-for-conservation#close/|publisher=[[World Wildlife Fund]]|accessdate=24 December 2015}}</ref> And, in his April 2015 interview with Yale Environment 360, he said, \"The environmental emergency that we face is not just a scientific issue, nor is it just a political issue, it is also a moral issue. And therefore all of us approaching this issue have to pick up our share of the responsibility to find and implement solutions. The scientific aspect of it, of course, is the supply of information \u2014 the creation of models and predictions and the introduction of techniques that we can use to remedy this. But our share of this responsibility is to take what scientists teach us to heart, so we actually transform our way of life into one that is sustainable.\u201d<ref>\"For Buddhist Leader, Religion And the Environment Are One\" Interview with H.H. The Karmapa by Roger Rohn, Yale Environment 360, 16 April 2015. [http://e360.yale.edu/feature/for_buddhist_leader_religion_and_the_environment_are_one/2866/]</ref>\n\n== Bibliography==\n'''2018-2019: Freedom through Meditation''' ([http://www.ktdpublications.com/freedom-through-meditation/ print] | [https://dharmaebooks.org/freedom-through-meditation/ ebook])\n\n*[https://dharmaebooks.org/at-vinde-frihed-gennem-meditation/ At vinde Frihed gennem Meditation]\n*[https://dharmaebooks.org/la-liberte-par-la-meditation/ La libert\u00e9 par la m\u00e9ditation]\n*[https://dharmaebooks.org/wolnosc-przez-medytacje/ Wolno\u015b\u0107 przez medytacj\u0119]\n*[https://dharmaebooks.org/freedom-meditation-russian/ \u0421\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0431\u043b\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0440\u044f \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438]\n*[https://dharmaebooks.org/wolnosc-przez-medytacje/ Wolno\u015b\u0107 przez medytacj\u0119]\n\n'''2008-2019: [https://www.namsebangdzo.com/Heart-Advice-of-the-Karmapa-p/15619.htm Heart Advice of the Karmapa]'''\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/loi-khuyen-tu-trai-tim-cua-duc-karmapa/ L\u1eddi khuy\u00ean t\u1eeb tr\u00e1i tim c\u1ee7a \u0110\u1ee9c Karmapa]\n\n'''2011-2019: Compassion Now!''' ([http://www.ktdpublications.com/compassion-now/ print] | [https://dharmaebooks.org/compassion-now/ ebook])\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/czas-na-wspolczucie/ Czas na wsp\u00f3\u0142czucie]\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/przyszlosc-jest-teraz/ Przysz\u0142o\u015b\u0107 jest teraz]\n\n'''2012-2019: The First Karmapa: The Life and Teachings of D\u00fcsum Khyenpa''' ([http://www.ktdpublications.com/the-first-karmapa/ print] | [https://dharmaebooks.org/the-first-karmapa/ ebook])\n\n'''2019: [https://dharmaebooks.org/ngondro-chariot/ The Chariot that Travels the Noble Path]'''\n\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/le-chariot/ Le Chariot pour parcourir la Noble Voie]\n* [https://dharmaebooks.org/ngondro-russian/ \u041a\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u043f\u0443\u0442\u0438 \u0431\u043b\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0445]\n\n'''2010-2019: Ngondro for Our Current Day: A Short Ngondro Practice and Its Instructions''' ([https://www.ktdpublications.com/ngondro-for-our-current-day/ print] | [https://dharmaebooks.org/ngondro-fo