{"title_page": "Al Jadeed", "text_new": "{{hatnote|For the television station in Perth, Australia, see [[NEW (TV station)]]}}\n{{hatnote|For the television station in Newton, Massachusetts, see [[NewTV]]}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Primary sources|date=May 2018}}\n{{More citations needed|date=December 2012}}\n{{Notability|date=May 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox television channel\n| name              = Al Jadeed\n| logofile          = Al Jadeed.PNG\n| logosize          = 200px\n| logocaption       = \n| logoalt           = \n| logo2             = \n| launch            = {{start date and age|1992|df=yes}}\n| closed date       = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n| picture format    = [[576p]]\n| share             = \n| share as of       = \n| share source      = \n| network           = \n| owner             = Tahsin Khayat\n| parent            = \n| slogan            = \u0627\u0646\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\n| motto             = \n| country           = [[Lebanon]]\n| language          = [[Arabic language|Arabic]]\n| broadcast area    = \n| affiliates        = \n| headquarters      = Salim Salam, Beirut\n| former names      = New TV\n| replaced names    = \n| replaced by names = \n| sister names      = \n| timeshift names   = \n| website           = {{URL|www.aljadeed.tv}}\n| terr serv 1       = \n| terr chan 1       = \n| sat serv 1        = \n| sat chan 1        = \n| cable serv 1      = [[Numericable]] (France)\n| cable chan 1      = Channel 721 (SD)\n| cable serv 2 = [[Ooredoo|Mozaic TV]] {{small|(Qatar)}}\n| cable chan 2 = Channel 143 (SD)\n| sat radio serv 1  = \n| sat radio chan 1  = \n| iptv serv 1       = [[Free (ISP)|Freebox TV]] (France)\n| iptv chan 1       = Channel 658 (SD)\n| online serv 1     = \n| online chan 1     = \n| 3gmobile serv 1   = \n}}\n\n'''''Al Jadeed''''' ({{lang-ar|\u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f}}, {{lang-en|New TV}}) is a Lebanese secular pan-Arab TV station. Based in [[Beirut]], it is one of the leading TV channels in Lebanon and the Levant. It was launched in 1992 and closed in 1997 due to Syrian intervention, and then relaunched in 2001 during a luxurious celebration attended by prominent figures. Al Jadeed today is considered one of the 3 leading TV channels in Lebanon (all 3 of which are the only mainstream channels in Lebanon not owned by the government or any political parties, regardless of political affiliation).\n\nOn 9 May 2005, ''Al Jadeed'' was also launched in [[Americas|America]] and the [[Pacific]], reaching Arab speaking immigrants in the United States, Canada, [[South America]] and Australia.<ref name=\"mysat\">{{cite web|title=Al Jadeed |url=http://mysat.tv/TVChannels/AlJadeed/tabid/126/Default.aspx |publisher=Mysat.tv |accessdate=22 July 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419020754/http://mysat.tv/TVChannels/AlJadeed/tabid/126/Default.aspx |archivedate=19 April 2012 }}</ref> As of 2012, it has become available for viewers in South America through [[Over-the-top content|over-the-top technology]] on [[MyTV (Arabic)|myTV]].\n\nIn 2007, a copyright issue arose with the name \u201cNew TV\u201d and the channel Arabized its name, to which it became Al Jadeed TV. The station is owned by Tahsin Khayat<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljadeed.tv/arabic/about-us/aljadeed-history|title=\u062a\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062e \u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f|website=AlJadeed.tv|language=en|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>. \n\n==History==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\n\n=== From 1991 to 1996: New TV ===\nUp to 1996, New TV was regularly in conflict with the ruling leaders.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\nAt the end of 1996, the Lebanese Ministry of Information decided to shut many TV stations, including New TV, the only secular broadcaster in Lebanese. Only five channels then got the right to broadcast, obviously chosen according to match religious communities\u2019 demands.\n\n=== Since 2001: ''Al Jadeed TV'' ===\nFrom 2000, New TV received a licence again and it became ''Al Jadeed'' TV in 2001.\n\n==Attacks, threats and intimidation attempts against ''Al Jadeed'' TV ==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\n\n=== Broadcasting suspended in 2003 ===\nIn January 2003, Information Ministry [[Michel Samaha]] ordered to hold the broadcasting of ''Al Jadeed'' TV's programs. This decision involved the Bila Rakeeb weekly program that had been advertising on revelations about [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{Citation|title=\u062a\u0648\u0642\u064a\u0641 \u062d\u0644\u0642\u0629 \u0628\u0644\u0627 \u0631\u0642\u064a\u0628 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f\u064a\u0629|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x0VWRTwMe6M|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Chairman arrested in 2003 ===\nOn December 7, 2003, [[Tahseen Khayat]], ''Al Jadeed'' TV's Chairman was arrested at home and held in custody for two days.<ref>{{Citation|title=\u0627\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0642 \u0633\u0631\u0627\u062d \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0630 \u062a\u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u064a\u0627\u0637 \u0628\u0639\u062f 48 \u0633\u0627\u0639\u0629|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aCF6ZuXl9sU|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> The channel's offices and Tahseen Khayat's home were searched.\n\n=== Threats against a female anchor in 2003 ===\nIn July 2003, ''Al Jadeed'' TV broadcast a new documentary involving the Lebanese General [[Jamil Al Sayyed|Jamil El Sayed]] in a corruption case with [[Syria]]. Most of the channel's managers were summoned to the Tribunal of Beirut. Among them was [[Dalia Ahmad]], a famous anchor. As a non-Lebanese, her work permit was withdrawn and she was then told she could work for any other Lebanese TV station but not ''Al Jadeed''. She finally resigned in December 2003. She then worked in the United States for [[Alhurra|Al Hurra]] and eventually came back to ''Al Jadeed'' TV after Jamil Al Sayed's arrest in October 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fanoos.com/society/dalia_ahmad.html|title=Dalia Ahmad|website=fanoos.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-lebanon-tribunal-generals-facts-idUSTRE53S4KF20090429|title=FACTBOX: Lebanese generals ordered released by Hariri court|date=2009-04-29|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en}}</ref> Independently from this case, she resigned again in 2018 and came back to the station in 2019.\n\n=== El Suddik case in 2006 ===\nIn December 2006, three ''Al Jadeed'' reporters were arrested following their investigation into the former Prime Minister [[Rafic Hariri]]\u2019s assassination and their lead on [[Muhammad Zuhair El Suddik]], one of the [[false witnesses]]. They were jailed for 45 days and released after their report was broadcast.<ref>{{Citation|title=\u062a\u0648\u0642\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0645\u0644\u0627\u0621 \u0641\u0631\u0627\u0633 \u062d\u0627\u0637\u0648\u0645 \u0648 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u062e\u064a\u0627\u0637 \u0648\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0631\u0628\u0631 \u0641\u064a \u0642\u0636\u064a\u0629 \u0645\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0647\u0648\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0648\u0631 \u0644\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u064a\u0629-2|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EsxyjuXKEOs|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Attack against the Chairman's house ===\nIn March 2010, a hundred members of the [[Druze]] community surrounded Tahseen Khayat\u2019s house and threatened to set fire to it. Although they did some damage to the house, they eventually withdrew after the Druze leader [[Walid Jumblat]] intervened.\n\n=== Murder of an ''Al Jadeed'' cameraman ===\nOn April 9th, 2012, an ''Al Jadeed'' crew went to northern Lebanon along the Syrian border. They were then fired at by the Syrian forces. [[Ali Shaaban]] was killed while Hussein Khreiss and Abed Khayat were seriously injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-lebanon-idUSBRE8380DX20120409|title=TV cameraman shot dead on Lebanon-Syria border|date=2012-04-09|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-04|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.unesco.org/news/director-general-denounces-killing-lebanese-tv-cameraman-ali-shaaban-border-syria|title=Director-General denounces killing of Lebanese TV cameraman Ali Shaaban on the border with Syria|date=2012-04-20|website=UNESCO|language=en|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/lebanese-tv-cameraman-shot-dead-syrian-border|title=Lebanese TV cameraman shot dead on Syrian border {{!}} Reporters without borders|date=2012-04-11|website=RSF|language=en|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Assault against Al Jadeed headquarters in 2012 ===\n{{One source|date=May 2018}}\nIn June 2012, masked men set fire to tires in front of ''Al Jadeed''\u2019s office\u2019s main door after the channel had released an interview with [[Ahmad Al-Aseer]], a Sunni Sheikh. ''Al Jadeed''\u2019s security team arrested one of the men.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Local-News/2012/Jul-02/179066-suspect-in-al-jadeed-tv-station-attack-accused-of-attempted-murder.ashx#axzz2lrMeZ1DC |title=Suspect in Al-Jadeed TV station attack accused of attempted murder|newspaper=[[The Daily Star (Lebanon)]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/world/leading-lebanese-tv-station-attacked-in-beirut|title=Leading Lebanese TV station attacked in Beirut|date=2015-03-26|website=[[Fox News]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Grenade attack against Al Jadeed headquarters in 2019 ===\nIn February 2019, the TV station was attacked with a hand grenade thrown out of a car. The suspects were affiliated with the Lebanese Progressive Socialist Party, to which the party\u2019s leader Walid Jounblatt later allowed authorities to arrest them and had a dinner with the channel\u2019s owner Tahsin Khayyat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/02/assailants-target-lebanese-tv-station-al-jadeed-hand-grenade-190202094746294.html|title=Assailants target Lebanese TV station Al Jadeed with hand grenade|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cpj.org/2019/02/unknown-assailants-attack-lebanese-tv-station-with.php|title=Unknown assailants attack Lebanese TV station with hand grenade|last=Avenue|first=Committee to Protect Journalists 330 7th|last2=York|first2=11th Floor New|website=cpj.org|language=en|access-date=2019-08-03|last3=Ny 10001}}</ref>\n\n== Legal attacks: Prosecution against ''Al Jadeed'' TV by the Special Tribunal for Lebanon ==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\nIn January 2014, the [[Special Tribunal for Lebanon]]  (a [[UN]] mandated tribunal set to judge [[Rafic Hariri]]\u2019s murderers) issued an order in lieu of indictment against the journalist [[Karma Khayat]] and ''Al Jadeed'' TV for whom she was the information programs director at the time of the incriminated facts. The Lebanese journalist and the channel are accused of contempt charges and justice obstruction after they released compromising information regarding the witnesses\u2019 protection system of the tribunal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/14/world/middleeast/lebanese-tv-executive-is-summoned-to-hague-court.html|title=Lebanese TV Executive Is Summoned to Hague Court|last=Simons|first=Marlise|date=2014-05-13|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2012, ''Al Jadeed'' TV had broadcast a 5 episodes documentary showing serious failures inside the tribunal related to the anonymity of the witnesses and their protection. Beside, the channel's teams had taken all the necessary measures to keep the interrogated persons anonymous (blurred faces, no name given).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rfi.fr/emission/20150411-karma-khayat-journaliste-libanaise-poursuivie-outrage-le-tsl-pays-bas-liban-justice-medias/|title=Chronique des droits de l'homme - Karma Khayat, journaliste libanaise poursuivie pour outrage par le TSL|date=2015-04-11|website=RFI|language=fr|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\nA year and a half later, Karma Khayat and ''Al Jadeed'' TV are being prosecuted for \u201cundermining the confidence of the public in the ability of the tribunal to protect confidential information related to the witnesses or alleged witnesses\u201d and to have disobeyed the order given by the Judge to stop broadcasting the reportage. They appeared in the court first in May 2014 for the pre-trial. The trial began on April 16, 2015 in [[The Hague]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stl-tsl.org/en/the-cases/contempt-cases/stl-14-05|title=Al Jadeed S.A.L. & Ms Khayat (STL-14-05)|website=www.stl-tsl.org|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\nKarma Khayat could be sentenced up to 7 years in jail and fined \u20ac100,000. Moreover, despite the tribunal's contradictions, this is the first time an organisation is prosecuted by an international tribunal which could make a precedent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lawgazette.co.uk/commentary-and-opinion/a-hague-tribunal-on-the-wrong-track/5048098.article|title=A Hague tribunal on the wrong track|last=Reyes2015-04-08T11:47:00+01:00|first=Eduardo|website=Law Gazette|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\n== Programming ==\n=== Talk shows ===\n* ''Kaw\u0101l\u012bs al-Mad\u012bna''\n* ''\u2019\u016al Nsh\u0101lla''\n\n=== Soap operas ===\n* ''[[G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015f (TV series)|G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015f]]''\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of journalists killed during the Syrian civil war]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Television in Lebanon}}\n{{Panama Papers leak}}\n{{Portal bar|Economics|Journalism|Politics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Al Jadeed}}\n[[Category:2001 establishments in Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2001]]\n[[Category:International broadcasters]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Media in Beirut]]\n[[Category:Arabic-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Beirut]]\n", "text_old": "{{hatnote|For the television station in Perth, Australia, see [[NEW (TV station)]]}}\n{{hatnote|For the television station in Newton, Massachusetts, see [[NewTV]]}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Primary sources|date=May 2018}}\n{{More citations needed|date=December 2012}}\n{{Notability|date=May 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox television channel\n| name              = Al Jadeed\n| logofile          = Al Jadeed.PNG\n| logosize          = 200px\n| logocaption       = \n| logoalt           = \n| logo2             = \n| launch            = {{start date and age|1992|df=yes}}\n| closed date       = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} -->\n| picture format    = [[576p]]\n| share             = \n| share as of       = \n| share source      = \n| network           = \n| owner             = Tahsin Khayat\n| parent            = \n| slogan            = \u0627\u0646\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\n| motto             = \n| country           = [[Lebanon]]\n| language          = [[Arabic language|Arabic]]\n| broadcast area    = \n| affiliates        = \n| headquarters      = Salim Salam, Beirut\n| former names      = New TV\n| replaced names    = \n| replaced by names = \n| sister names      = \n| timeshift names   = \n| website           = {{URL|www.aljadeed.tv}}\n| terr serv 1       = \n| terr chan 1       = \n| sat serv 1        = \n| sat chan 1        = \n| cable serv 1      = [[Numericable]] (France)\n| cable chan 1      = Channel 721 (SD)\n| cable serv 2 = [[Ooredoo|Mozaic TV]] {{small|(Qatar)}}\n| cable chan 2 = Channel 143 (SD)\n| sat radio serv 1  = \n| sat radio chan 1  = \n| iptv serv 1       = [[Free (ISP)|Freebox TV]] (France)\n| iptv chan 1       = Channel 658 (SD)\n| online serv 1     = \n| online chan 1     = \n| 3gmobile serv 1   = \n}}\n\n'''''Al Jadeed''''' ({{lang-ar|\u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f}}, {{lang-en|New TV}}) is a Lebanese secular pan-Arab TV station. Based in [[Beirut]], it is one of the leading TV channels in Lebanon and the Levant. It was launched in 1992 and closed in 1997 due to Syrian intervention, and then relaunched in 2001 during a luxurious celebration attended by prominent figures. Al Jadeed today is considered one of the 3 leading TV channels in Lebanon (all 3 of which are the only mainstream channels in Lebanon not owned by the government or any political parties, regardless of political affiliation).\n\nOn 9 May 2005, ''Al Jadeed'' was also launched in [[Americas|America]] and the [[Pacific]], reaching Arab speaking immigrants in the United States, Canada, [[South America]] and Australia.<ref name=\"mysat\">{{cite web|title=Al Jadeed |url=http://mysat.tv/TVChannels/AlJadeed/tabid/126/Default.aspx |publisher=Mysat.tv |accessdate=22 July 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419020754/http://mysat.tv/TVChannels/AlJadeed/tabid/126/Default.aspx |archivedate=19 April 2012 }}</ref> As of 2012, it has become available for viewers in South America through [[Over-the-top content|over-the-top technology]] on [[MyTV (Arabic)|myTV]].\n\nIn 2007, a copyright issue arose with the name \u201cNew TV\u201d and the channel Arabized its name, to which it became Al Jadeed TV. The station is owned by Tahsin Khayat<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljadeed.tv/arabic/about-us/aljadeed-history|title=\u062a\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062e \u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f|website=AlJadeed.tv|language=en|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>. \n\n==History==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\n\n=== From 1991 to 1996: New TV ===\nUp to 1996, New TV was regularly in conflict with the ruling leaders.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\nAt the end of 1996, the Lebanese Ministry of Information decided to shut many TV stations, including New TV, the only secular broadcaster in Lebanese. Only five channels then got the right to broadcast, obviously chosen according to match religious communities\u2019 demands.\n\n=== Since 2001: ''Al Jadeed TV'' ===\nFrom 2000, New TV received a licence again and it became ''Al Jadeed'' TV in 2001.\n\n==Attacks, threats and intimidation attempts against ''Al Jadeed'' TV ==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\n\n=== Broadcasting suspended in 2003 ===\nIn January 2003, Information Ministry [[Michel Samaha]] ordered to hold the broadcasting of ''Al Jadeed'' TV's programs. This decision involved the Bila Rakeeb weekly program that had been advertising on revelations about [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{Citation|title=\u062a\u0648\u0642\u064a\u0641 \u062d\u0644\u0642\u0629 \u0628\u0644\u0627 \u0631\u0642\u064a\u0628 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f\u064a\u0629|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x0VWRTwMe6M|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Chairman arrested in 2003 ===\nOn December 7, 2003, [[Tahseen Khayat]], ''Al Jadeed'' TV's Chairman was arrested at home and held in custody for two days.<ref>{{Citation|title=\u0627\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0642 \u0633\u0631\u0627\u062d \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0630 \u062a\u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u064a\u0627\u0637 \u0628\u0639\u062f 48 \u0633\u0627\u0639\u0629|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aCF6ZuXl9sU|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> The channel's offices and Tahseen Khayat's home were searched.\n\n=== Threats against a female anchor in 2003 ===\nIn July 2003, ''Al Jadeed'' TV broadcast a new documentary involving the Lebanese General [[Jamil Al Sayyed|Jamil El Sayed]] in a corruption case with [[Syria]]. Most of the channel's managers were summoned to the Tribunal of Beirut. Among them was [[Dalia Ahmad]], a famous anchor. As a non-Lebanese, her work permit was withdrawn and she was then told she could work for any other Lebanese TV station but not ''Al Jadeed''. She finally resigned in December 2003. She then worked in the United States for [[Alhurra|Al Hurra]] and eventually came back to ''Al Jadeed'' TV after Jamil Al Sayed's arrest in October 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fanoos.com/society/dalia_ahmad.html|title=Dalia Ahmad|website=fanoos.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-lebanon-tribunal-generals-facts-idUSTRE53S4KF20090429|title=FACTBOX: Lebanese generals ordered released by Hariri court|date=2009-04-29|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en}}</ref> Independently from this case, she resigned again in 2018 and came back to the station in 2019.\n\n=== El Suddik case in 2006 ===\nIn December 2006, three ''Al Jadeed'' reporters were arrested following their investigation into the former Prime Minister [[Rafic Hariri]]\u2019s assassination and their lead on [[Muhammad Zuhair El Suddik]], one of the [[false witnesses]]. They were jailed for 45 days and released after their report was broadcast.<ref>{{Citation|title=\u062a\u0648\u0642\u064a\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0645\u0644\u0627\u0621 \u0641\u0631\u0627\u0633 \u062d\u0627\u0637\u0648\u0645 \u0648 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u062e\u064a\u0627\u0637 \u0648\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0631\u0628\u0631 \u0641\u064a \u0642\u0636\u064a\u0629 \u0645\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0647\u0648\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0648\u0631 \u0644\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u064a\u0629-2|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EsxyjuXKEOs|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Attack against the Chairman's house ===\nIn March 2010, a hundred members of the [[Druze]] community surrounded Tahseen Khayat\u2019s house and threatened to set fire to it. Although they did some damage to the house, they eventually withdrew after the Druze leader [[Walid Jumblat]] intervened.\n\n=== Murder of an ''Al Jadeed'' cameraman ===\nOn April 9th, 2012, an ''Al Jadeed'' crew went to northern Lebanon along the Syrian border. They were then fired at by the Syrian forces. [[Ali Shaaban]] was killed while Hussein Khreiss and Abed Khayat were seriously injured.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-lebanon-idUSBRE8380DX20120409|title=TV cameraman shot dead on Lebanon-Syria border|date=2012-04-09|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-08-04|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.unesco.org/news/director-general-denounces-killing-lebanese-tv-cameraman-ali-shaaban-border-syria|title=Director-General denounces killing of Lebanese TV cameraman Ali Shaaban on the border with Syria|date=2012-04-20|website=UNESCO|language=en|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rsf.org/en/news/lebanese-tv-cameraman-shot-dead-syrian-border|title=Lebanese TV cameraman shot dead on Syrian border {{!}} Reporters without borders|date=2012-04-11|website=RSF|language=en|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Assault against Al Jadeed headquarters in 2012 ===\n{{One source|date=May 2018}}\nIn June 2012, masked men set fire to tires in front of ''Al Jadeed''\u2019s office\u2019s main door after the channel had released an interview with [[Ahma Al-Aseer]], a Sunni Sheikh. ''Al Jadeed''\u2019s security team arrested one of the men.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/News/Local-News/2012/Jul-02/179066-suspect-in-al-jadeed-tv-station-attack-accused-of-attempted-murder.ashx#axzz2lrMeZ1DC |title=Suspect in Al-Jadeed TV station attack accused of attempted murder|newspaper=[[The Daily Star (Lebanon)]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/world/leading-lebanese-tv-station-attacked-in-beirut|title=Leading Lebanese TV station attacked in Beirut|date=2015-03-26|website=[[Fox News]]|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref>\n\n=== Grenade attack against Al Jadeed headquarters in 2019 ===\nIn February 2019, the TV station was attacked with a hand grenade thrown out of a car. The suspects were affiliated with the Lebanese Progressive Socialist Party, to which the party\u2019s leader Walid Jounblatt later allowed authorities to arrest them and had a dinner with the channel\u2019s owner Tahsin Khayyat.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/02/assailants-target-lebanese-tv-station-al-jadeed-hand-grenade-190202094746294.html|title=Assailants target Lebanese TV station Al Jadeed with hand grenade|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=2019-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cpj.org/2019/02/unknown-assailants-attack-lebanese-tv-station-with.php|title=Unknown assailants attack Lebanese TV station with hand grenade|last=Avenue|first=Committee to Protect Journalists 330 7th|last2=York|first2=11th Floor New|website=cpj.org|language=en|access-date=2019-08-03|last3=Ny 10001}}</ref>\n\n== Legal attacks: Prosecution against ''Al Jadeed'' TV by the Special Tribunal for Lebanon ==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2018}}\nIn January 2014, the [[Special Tribunal for Lebanon]]  (a [[UN]] mandated tribunal set to judge [[Rafic Hariri]]\u2019s murderers) issued an order in lieu of indictment against the journalist [[Karma Khayat]] and ''Al Jadeed'' TV for whom she was the information programs director at the time of the incriminated facts. The Lebanese journalist and the channel are accused of contempt charges and justice obstruction after they released compromising information regarding the witnesses\u2019 protection system of the tribunal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/14/world/middleeast/lebanese-tv-executive-is-summoned-to-hague-court.html|title=Lebanese TV Executive Is Summoned to Hague Court|last=Simons|first=Marlise|date=2014-05-13|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-05|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2012, ''Al Jadeed'' TV had broadcast a 5 episodes documentary showing serious failures inside the tribunal related to the anonymity of the witnesses and their protection. Beside, the channel's teams had taken all the necessary measures to keep the interrogated persons anonymous (blurred faces, no name given).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rfi.fr/emission/20150411-karma-khayat-journaliste-libanaise-poursuivie-outrage-le-tsl-pays-bas-liban-justice-medias/|title=Chronique des droits de l'homme - Karma Khayat, journaliste libanaise poursuivie pour outrage par le TSL|date=2015-04-11|website=RFI|language=fr|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\nA year and a half later, Karma Khayat and ''Al Jadeed'' TV are being prosecuted for \u201cundermining the confidence of the public in the ability of the tribunal to protect confidential information related to the witnesses or alleged witnesses\u201d and to have disobeyed the order given by the Judge to stop broadcasting the reportage. They appeared in the court first in May 2014 for the pre-trial. The trial began on April 16, 2015 in [[The Hague]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stl-tsl.org/en/the-cases/contempt-cases/stl-14-05|title=Al Jadeed S.A.L. & Ms Khayat (STL-14-05)|website=www.stl-tsl.org|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\nKarma Khayat could be sentenced up to 7 years in jail and fined \u20ac100,000. Moreover, despite the tribunal's contradictions, this is the first time an organisation is prosecuted by an international tribunal which could make a precedent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lawgazette.co.uk/commentary-and-opinion/a-hague-tribunal-on-the-wrong-track/5048098.article|title=A Hague tribunal on the wrong track|last=Reyes2015-04-08T11:47:00+01:00|first=Eduardo|website=Law Gazette|language=en|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref>\n\n== Programming ==\n=== Talk shows ===\n* ''Kaw\u0101l\u012bs al-Mad\u012bna''\n* ''\u2019\u016al Nsh\u0101lla''\n\n=== Soap operas ===\n* ''[[G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015f (TV series)|G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015f]]''\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of journalists killed during the Syrian civil war]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Television in Lebanon}}\n{{Panama Papers leak}}\n{{Portal bar|Economics|Journalism|Politics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Al Jadeed}}\n[[Category:2001 establishments in Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2001]]\n[[Category:International broadcasters]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Lebanon]]\n[[Category:Media in Beirut]]\n[[Category:Arabic-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Beirut]]\n", "name_user": "Wossodan", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAssault against Al Jadeed headquarters in 2012", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al_Jadeed"}
{"title_page": "Tarun Chandra", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| bgcolour      = \n| name          = Taarun Chandrra\n| image         =https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=i&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=imgres&cd=&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwj9z_vemszKAhWJWhoKHZRuCXYQjRwICTAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.galatta.com%2Fkannada%2Fphotos%2Flargeimage%2Factor%2Ftarun-chandra%2F16850%2F&psig=AFQjCNF3N_I2_jZmuFfIjV2KgXOnhAQzZQ&ust=1454060267414205 \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birthname     = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|4|27}}\n| birth_place    = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| othername     = \n| yearsactive   = 2003-present\n| homepage      = \n| occupation    = [[Actor]]\n}}\n\n'''Tarun Chandra''' ({{lang-kn|\u0ca4\u0cb0\u0cc1\u0ca3\u0ccd \u0c9a\u0c82\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0cb0}}; born 27 April 1983), [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] credited as '''Tarun''', is an [[India]]n film actor based in [[Kannada cinema|Kannada Film Industry]]. He made his film debut in the multi-starrer ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' (2003) and has since then acted in various films, notably being, ''Geleya'' (2007), ''[[Love Guru (Kannada film)|Love Guru]]'' (2008) and ''[[Gaana Bajaana]]'' (2010).\n\n== Early life ==\nTarun was born in Bangalore. He graduated his B.Com degree in MES College, Bangalore. He underwent three months acting course at Kishore Namit Kapoor Acting Institute, before he entered into films. He first appeared as one of the lead actors in 2003 released film, ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]''. After Geleya, Hani Hani's successful run, he was approached for Parichaya and by director Prashant for his movie ''[[Love Guru]]'', which won a state award for best movie.<ref>http://entertainment.oneindia.in/kannada/news/2010/tarun-chandra-interview-gaana-bajaana-271010.html</ref> He had also acted in a Telugu film Valliddari Vayasu Padahare which was released in 2006.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' ||  ||                  \n|-\n| 2006 || ''Valliddari Vayasu Padahare'' || Vamsee || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Geleya]]'' || Vishwa ||  \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Ee Bandhana]]'' ||  ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Hani Hani (film)|Hani Hani]]'' || Rahul ||                \n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Love Guru (Kannada film)|Love Guru]]'' || Pratham ||\n|-\n| 2009 ||''Parichaya'' || Jayanth  ||          \n|-\n| 2009 || ''Seena'' || Seena ||  \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Gaana Bajaana]]'' || Krish || \n|- \n| 2011 || ''Naanalla'' || Siddharth ||\n|- \n| 2011 || ''Achu Mechu'' || Vijay ||\n|-\n| 2012|| ''[[Addhuri]]'' || Tarun  || Guest appearance\n|-   \n| 2012 || ''[[Ondu Kshanadalli]]'' || Shyam || \n|-\n| 2012 || ''[[Snehitaru]]'' ||  || \n|-\n| 2013 || ''Pade Pade'' || Sunny || \n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Gharshane]]'' || Himself || Special appearance\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Goa (2015 film)|Goa]]'' || || \n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|3749070/}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chandra, Tarun}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2015}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| bgcolour      = \n| name          = Tarun Chandra\n| image         =https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=i&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=imgres&cd=&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0ahUKEwj9z_vemszKAhWJWhoKHZRuCXYQjRwICTAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.galatta.com%2Fkannada%2Fphotos%2Flargeimage%2Factor%2Ftarun-chandra%2F16850%2F&psig=AFQjCNF3N_I2_jZmuFfIjV2KgXOnhAQzZQ&ust=1454060267414205 \n| imagesize     = \n| caption       = \n| birthname     = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|4|27}}\n| birth_place    = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| othername     = \n| yearsactive   = 2003-present\n| homepage      = \n| occupation    = [[Actor]]\n}}\n\n'''Tarun Chandra''' ({{lang-kn|\u0ca4\u0cb0\u0cc1\u0ca3\u0ccd \u0c9a\u0c82\u0ca6\u0ccd\u0cb0}}; born 27 April 1983), [[Mononymous person|mononymously]] credited as '''Tarun''', is an [[India]]n film actor based in [[Kannada cinema|Kannada Film Industry]]. He made his film debut in the multi-starrer ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' (2003) and has since then acted in various films, notably being, ''Geleya'' (2007), ''[[Love Guru (Kannada film)|Love Guru]]'' (2008) and ''[[Gaana Bajaana]]'' (2010).\n\n== Early life ==\nTarun was born in Bangalore. He graduated his B.Com degree in MES College, Bangalore. He underwent three months acting course at Kishore Namit Kapoor Acting Institute, before he entered into films. He first appeared as one of the lead actors in 2003 released film, ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]''. After Geleya, Hani Hani's successful run, he was approached for Parichaya and by director Prashant for his movie ''[[Love Guru]]'', which won a state award for best movie.<ref>http://entertainment.oneindia.in/kannada/news/2010/tarun-chandra-interview-gaana-bajaana-271010.html</ref> He had also acted in a Telugu film Valliddari Vayasu Padahare which was released in 2006.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Khushi (2003 Kannada film)|Khushi]]'' ||  ||                  \n|-\n| 2006 || ''Valliddari Vayasu Padahare'' || Vamsee || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Geleya]]'' || Vishwa ||  \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Ee Bandhana]]'' ||  ||\n|-\n| 2008 